# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback for real navigation routes.
# Any path with no real static asset is served index.html (HTTP 200) so React
# Router can resolve client-side routes on hard-refresh, deep links, and
# email/OAuth callback URLs.
#
# MISSING /assets/* chunks are deliberately NOT handled here — they are handled
# by functions/assets/[[path]].ts, which returns a REAL 404. Cloudflare
# _redirects CANNOT return a 404 status (it supports only 200 rewrites and 3xx
# redirects), which is why the previous `/assets/* /index.html 404` rule silently
# fell through to this `/* 200` catch-all and the app kept white-screening on
# poisoned immutable caches during deploy propagation (2026-07-06 incident,
# re-confirmed 2026-07-10: a dead /assets/*.js URL was still answering 200
# text/html in production). A real 404.html at the Pages root is also not an
# option — it disables the SPA fallback and 404s every /app/* route and the
# OAuth callback. Full writeup: functions/assets/[[path]].ts.
/*    /index.html   200
